eva

Interface Attribute


  • public interface Attribute
    The Attribute interface provides a programatic representation of a schema attribute.

    Attributes are loaded into memory, and it is generally more efficient to access attribute information via this interface.

    • Method Detail

      • cardinality

        java.lang.Object cardinality()
        Provides the cardinality of the attribute.
        Returns:
        either CARDINALITY_ONE or CARDINALITY_MANY

      • hasFullText

        boolean hasFullText()
        Unsupported.
        Returns:
        true if attribute has :db/fulltext true

      • hasNoHistory

        boolean hasNoHistory()
        Unsupported.
        Returns:
        true if attribute has :db/noHistory true

      • id

        java.lang.Object id()
        Entity id of the attribute.
        Returns:
        entity id

      • ident

        java.lang.Object ident()
        Human readable keyword that identifies the attribute.
        Returns:
        keyword identifier

      • isComponent

        boolean isComponent()
        Tests if the reference attribute is a component-attribute.

        This indicates that the referenced entity is considered "a part of" the referencing entity.

        Returns:
        true if attribute has :db/isComponent true

      • isIndexed

        boolean isIndexed()
        Indicates if the attribute value are indexed.

        This allows efficient searches by attribute value. By default, all attributes are indexed (except when of type :db.type/bytes)

        Returns:
        true if attribute DOES NOT have :db/index false or :db/valueType :db.type/bytes

      • hasAVET

        boolean hasAVET()
        Indicates if the attribute is in the AVET index. Unlike Datomic, this is always true if isIndexed() is true.
        Returns:
        true if isIndexed() is true

      • unique

        java.lang.Object unique()
        Indicates if the attribute is unique, and if so, what type of uniqueness constraint is enforced.
        Returns:
        either UNIQUE_IDENTITY or UNIQUE_VALUE

      • valueType

        java.lang.Object valueType()
        The value type of the attribute.
        Returns:
        one of: TYPE_BIGDEC TYPE_BIGINT TYPE_BOOLEAN TYPE_BYTES TYPE_DOUBLE TYPE_FLOAT TYPE_FN TYPE_INSTANT TYPE_KEYWORD TYPE_LONG TYPE_REF TYPE_STRING TYPE_URI TYPE_UUID
